According to realtor website [[Zillow]], the average price of a home as of May 31, 2025, in Kindred is $411,489.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kindred, ND Housing Market |url=https://www.zillow.com/home-values/12199/kindred-nd/ |publisher=[[Zillow]] |access-date=July 20, 2025 |language=en}}</ref>

As of the 2023 [[American Community Survey]], there are 309 estimated households in Kindred with an average of 3.00 persons per household. The city has a median household income of $103,542. Approximately 2.8% of the city's population lives at or below the [[Poverty in the United States|poverty line]]. Kindred has an estimated 81.7% employment rate, with 43.1% of the population holding a bachelor's degree or higher and 99.4% holding a high school diploma.<ref name="QF">{{Cite web|title=U.S. Census Bureau QuickFacts: Kindred city, North Dakota |url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/kindredcitynorthdakota/PST045224 |access-date=July 20, 2025 |website=www.census.gov |language=en}}</ref>

The top five reported ancestries (people were allowed to report up to two ancestries, thus the figures will generally add to more than 100%) were English (95.3%), Spanish (0.8%), Indo-European (3.8%), Asian and Pacific Islander (0.0%), and Other (0.1%).

The median age in the city was 32.9 years.

