===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], there were 889 people, 313 households, and 236 families residing in the city.<ref>{{Cite web|title=US Census Bureau, Table P16: Household Type |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Kindred%20city,%20North%20Dakota%20p16&y=2020 |access-date=July 20, 2025 |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> The [[population density]] was {{convert|613.53|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 339 housing units at an average density of {{convert|233.95|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 95.84% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.22% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.45% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.00% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.00% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.79% from some other races and 2.70% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 2.14% of the population.<ref>{{Cite web|title=How many people live in Kindred city, North Dakota |url=https://data.usatoday.com/census/total-population/total-population-change/kindred-city-north-dakota/160-3842780/ |access-date=July 20, 2025 |publisher=USA Today}}</ref>

===2010 census===
As of the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]], there were 692 people, 267 households, and 185 families residing in the city. The population density was {{convert|477.90|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 289 housing units at an average density of {{convert|199.59|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 95.95% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.14% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.72% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.00% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.00% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 1.16% from some other races and 2.02% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 1.45% of the population.

There were 267 households, of which 44.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 56.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.6% had a female householder with no husband present, 4.5% had a male householder with no wife present, and 30.7% were non-families. 24.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.59 and the average family size was 3.16.

The median age in the city was 32.5 years. 33.1% of residents were under the age of 18; 5.4% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 30.9% were from 25 to 44; 20.8% were from 45 to 64; and 9.7% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the city was 50.3% male and 49.7% female.

===2000 census===
As of the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], there were 614 people, 248 households, and 167 families residing in the city. The population density was {{convert|615.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 267 housing units at an average density of {{convert|267.6|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 98.37% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.16% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.33% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.16% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.00% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.00% from some other races and 0.98% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 0.98% of the population.

There were 248 households, out of which 38.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 56.9% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 6.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 32.3% were non-families. 28.2% of all households were made up of individuals, and 12.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.48 and the average family size was 3.06.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 30.8% under the age of 18, 5.2% from 18 to 24, 35.0% from 25 to 44, 15.5% from 45 to 64, and 13.5% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 93.2 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $43,250, and the median income for a family was $49,091. Males had a median income of $31,607 versus $22,167 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $18,314. About 4.6% of families and 6.2% of the population were below the [[Poverty threshold|poverty line]], including 7.7% of those under age 18 and 8.8% of those age 65 or over.

